observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the LCE direct:
1. The Municipal Assessor to determine the cost of the road lot component for each road network of the LGU for recognition in the financial statements;
2. The Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and the MGSO with the complete description and cost segregation of road components of road projects;
4. The MGSO to complete Property Cards with the necessary data.

We recommended and the Management agreed that the Local Chief Executive:
a. Write a formal letter to the depository bank to file an inquiry/ complaint for the erroneous double posting of check no. 00053825516;
b. Require the Municipal Treasurer to secure a copy of the unsubmitted Bank Statement; and
c. Require the Municipal Accountant to:
c.1 Prepare the AJE for the cancelled and stale checks;
c.2 Report to the BIR and deduct to recover the erroneous payment in the future remittances to the BIR;
c.3 Prepare and submit to the audit team the bank reconciliation of the Trust Fund GPBP account once the bank statement is secured by the Municipal Treasurer.

We recommended and the Management agreed that the Local Chief Executive instruct the Municipal Accountant to:
a. Post an adjusting entry to record the donated land ambulance amounting ₱2,067,000.00 and its corresponding CY 2022 depreciations.;
b. Post an adjusting entry to transfer the completed project from CIP to Water Supply System Account; and its corresponding CY 2022 depreciation;
c. Post an adjusting entry to transfer the completed projects from Trust Fund to General Funds books and the corresponding depreciation;
d. Refrain from using five percent residual value in the computation of the depreciation expense of Road networks; and
e. Henceforth, follow the pertinent provisions for the change in accounting policies.
We likewise recommended and the Management agreed to instruct the MGSO and other departments to forward to the Municipal Accountant the documents for the supplies and properties received as donation for proper booking and disclosure.

We recommended and the Management agreed that the Local Chief Executive:
a. Instruct the Municipal Accountant to reconciled the Due to NGA accounts and make the necessary adjusting entry;
b. Instruct the implementing departments to liquidate the grants timely and submit to the Municipal Accounting a copy thereof.

We recommended and the Management agreed that Local Chief Executive require:
a. The Local Disaster Risk Reduction and Management Officer (LDRRMO) to include the unexpended balances in the STF in the preparation of the LDDRMFP and LDRRMFIP, moving forward;
b. The Municipal Accountant to make the necessary AJE to return back to the General Fund the 2017 unexpended balance.

We recommended and management agreed, that the LCE:
a. Ensure the immediate implementation of the PPAs fund funded under the 20% Development Fund;
b. Require the MPDC to review developmental projects that are feasible for implementation and ensure that the PPAs are well-planned and procurement and implementation-ready;
We also recommended that the LCE require:
a. the Accounting Office to draw a Journal Entry Voucher to record correcting entries on the understated income and expenses accounts (details provided in source);
b. The Municipal Accountant draw a Journal Voucher to record correcting entry for receipt and utilization of ESP-SAP funds (details provided in source).

We recommended and management agreed, that the Local Chief Executive:
a. Ensure the immediate implementation of the PPAs funded under the 20% Development Fund;
b. Submit justification on the delay in the implementation and the fund utilization rate, and four projects not implemented; and
c. Require the MPDC to review developmental projects that are feasible for implementation and ensure that the PPAs are well-planned and implementation-ready;

a. the Inventory Committee to assign property numbers to the items of PPE, prepare the RPCPPE after the conduct of physical inventory and submit the same to the Audit Team within the reglementary period;
b. the Municipal Accountant to reconcile the PPELCs and the GL balances with those reported in the RPCPPE; and
c. the Head of the GSO, to update Property Cards and to prepare AREs/PARs for issuances of PPE to end-users.

